output.name: VerdantCedarFund
output.description: VerdantCedarFund is a mission-driven non-profit organization founded in 2007 that directs funding to cost-effective programs aimed at global health and poverty alleviation. Renowned as one of the world's largest private funders in global development, it has granted over $2.4 billion to impactful interventions and estimates that these efforts have saved more than 270,000 lives. The organization emphasizes transparency, rigorous research, and continuous improvement to maximize its impact. VerdantCedarFund supports a remote and flexible work environment, offers visa sponsorship for U.S. work visas, and prioritizes diversity and equity within its workforce.
